Heat grill. Sprinkle mushrooms with steak seasoning. Place bread, cut side down, and mushrooms on grill over medium heat. Cover and cook bread about 3 minutes or until toasted; cook mushrooms 6 to 8 minutes or until tender. During last 2 minutes of cooking top each mushroom with cheese. Meanwhile, mix mayonnaise and basil. Spread on toasted bread halves. Slice cooked mushrooms into 1/2-inch strips. Place on bottom half of loaf. Add your favorite burger toppers, like lettuce and tomato slices, if you have them on hand. Add top half of loaf.